Since spring 2009, eCarus offers each semester about 50 students the possibility of applying their gained skills and knowledge on the construction of a real electric vehicle. The main objectives of this project are to increase technical expertise in the field of electric mobility on the one hand and to enable the students to gain experience in group work on the other hand.


The project eCarus is completely organized by students and therefore it offers students the opportunity to enhance their skills in self-reliance, teamwork, leadership and responsibility.


“What makes eCarus so special is the connection of theory and practice, technology and social skills applied to a highly active and exciting topic –electric mobility. ECarus offers me the unique opportunity to acquire competences for my future professional life.”

Seit dem Frühjahr 2009 bietet eCARus jedes Semester ca.50 Studierenden der Fakultät für Elektrotechnik und Informationstechnik der Technischen Universität München die Möglichkeit, die im Studium erlernten Inhalte beim Bau eines Elektrofahrzeugs anzuwenden. Die Hauptziele des Projekts sind einerseits die Stärkung der Fachkompetenz im Bereich Elektromobilität, anderseits erlernen die Studierenden die Fähigkeit teamübergreifend zu kooperieren.


The project eCarus is completely organized by students and therefore it offers students the opportunity to enhance their skills in self-reliance, teamwork, leadership and responsibility.


Das rein studentisch organisierte Projekt bietet den Studierenden die Möglichkeit ihre Fähigkeiten, u.a. in den Bereichen selbstständiges Arbeiten, Teamwork, Führung und Projekt Verantwortung, auszubauen.

Since spring 2009, eCarus offers each semester about 50 students the possibility of applying their gained skills and knowledge on the construction of a real electric vehicle. The main objectives of this project are to increase technical expertise in the field of electric mobility on the one hand and to enable the students to gain experience in group work on the other hand.


The project eCarus is completely organized by students and therefore it offers students the opportunity to enhance their skills in self-reliance, teamwork, leadership and responsibility.


“What makes eCarus so special is the connection of theory and practice, technology and social skills applied to a highly active and exciting topic –electric mobility. ECarus offers me the unique opportunity to acquire competences for my future professional life.”

Depuis 2009, offre eCARus ,chaque semestre, a environ 50 etudiants en electro-et informationtechnique la possibilite d'appliquer le contenu theorique du cours afin de construire une voiture electrique.


Le but de ce projet consiste a renforcer ses connaissances dans le domaine de l'electromobilite et d'ameliorer ses capacites a travailler en equipe. Certes, ce projet est destine en premier lieu a permettre aux etudiants de se former techniquement a travers le travail independant et socialement a travers le travail d'equipe, la direction et la responsabilite du projet.


"La particularite de eCARus se base sur l'alternance entre la theorie et la pratique , la technique et les competences sociales autour d'un theme attractif et actuel de nos jours qu'est: L'electromobilite. eCARus est une opportunite inegale de nous former pour integrer le monde du travail."
